            <h1 class="section-title">The Ranthambhore Project, India</h1>
            <%= image_tag "india2.jpg", :class => "img-responsive pull-right article-img"%>
            <h2>The expected outcomes of the Project are:</h2>  
              <p>In December 2010, during a visit to the Ranthambhore area Dr. Scott Haldeman, President of World Spine Care, met Dr. Governhan Singh Rathore, Executive Director of the Prakratik Society, which operates the Sevika Hospital in this area of India. It is the only hospital serving a population of nearly 250,000 inhabitants covering 96 villages along the Ranthambhore National Park in the State of Rajasthan, India.</p>
              <p>Dr. Governhan Singh Rathore agreed to assist World Spine Care in setting up a spine care clinic in the Sevika Hospital.  Dr. Geoff Outerbridge traveled to Ranthambhore in April 2011 to set up the World Spine Care clinic.</p>
              <p>At this time, there is no care available for patients with spinal conditions in this district of India other than traditional medicine and pain/anti-inflammatory medication.</p>
              <p>The Prakratik Society is currently building a new hospital with space for the WSC clinic and the project will be re-initiated once the hospital is complete. </p>           
